07/03/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The defence ministry received an official inquiry from the US State Department on Thursday (6 March), seeking clarification on the country's position on potential military action in Iraq. The daily </I>Utrinski Vesnik</I> quotes a source who says Washington asked Macedonia whether it would be willing to actively participate in a US and British-led coalition.
Also Thursday, Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and Chief of General Staff of the Army Metodi Stamboliski held a farewell meeting with Gen Gaetano Cigna, commander of NATO's Allied Harmony Mission. Afterwards, Cigna assured the public there would be no security vacuum during NATO's handover to the EU's rapid reaction force. (Utrinski Vesnik - 07/03/03)
